snippet.textDisplay:
I'd suggest have one bowl for wet food and one for dry food. Cats don't typically like mixed foods, but of course there are exceptions. Some cats love mixed foods.
The wet food is great to keep them hydrated, some cats get easily dehydrated.
Dry food is great for their teeth, it helps keep them in tip top shape.
Maybe give 1/4th of a can of wet twice a day, and leave 1/4th of a cup of dry food out. Idk about the actual servings; it's been too long since I worked with vets or experts in the field. You can still get what I'm saying though, divide the total amount of food she gets into threes, 2 of those will be wet food fed (one in morning, one at night), and the third will be dry food so she can graze.

Please make sure she is eating kitten food.. it is good for her developing kittens, also separate her wet food and dry food.. give her wet food once or twice a day and then give her access to the dry food all the time with her water

I personally think she still has a few more weeks to go, she will pear more out the closer she get to her due date.. also she will more than likely have her babies at night ( cats are nocturnal)

I have had many litters of kittens
